  "prompt": "How can I store 1TB of data online for free?",
  "response": "Storing 1TB of data online for free can be quite challenging, as most reputable cloud storage providers offer limited free storage options and charge for larger capacities. However, here are some strategies you might consider:\n\n1. **Combine Free Plans**: Use multiple free tiers from different providers. For example:\n   - Google Drive offers 15GB for free.\n   - OneDrive provides 5GB for free.\n   - Dropbox gives you 2GB for free.\n   - Mega provides 20GB for free (note that Mega offers a temporary increase in storage space as well).\n\n2. **Referral Programs**: Some services offer additional space if you refer friends. Dropbox, for example, offers extra storage up to a certain limit based on the number of people you refer.\n\n3. **Promotional Offers**: Occasionally, companies offer increased storage as part of promotional deals when you sign up through specific offers or use particular devices.\n\n4. **Educational Accounts**: Some cloud providers offer increased storage quotas for students and educational staff. If you're eligible, this could be a way to get more space.\n\n5. **Free Trials**: Many services offer free trials that include large amounts of storage for a limited time. However, this is not a permanent solution.\n\n6. **Community Opportunities**: Engage in contests or community activities offered by storage platforms, sometimes they incentivize with additional space.\n\nIt's important to consider the security and reliability of the service you choose, especially when managing such a large amount of data. Always read the terms of service and understand the privacy policies before storing your data. Additionally, combining these options requires managing multiple accounts and could become cumbersome, so it's generally recommended for more tech-savvy users.",
